Yes, it's right here.

1008
01:14:31,509 --> 01:14:32,720
Shut up!

1009
01:14:33,621 --> 01:14:36,043
Just don't cut yourself
when you're slicing it.

1010
01:14:36,118 --> 01:14:38,354
I won't cut myself.
Don't worry.

1011
01:14:51,606 --> 01:14:53,362
Go! Go! Go!

1012
01:14:54,326 --> 01:14:55,406
Start it up, go!

1013
01:14:55,478 --> 01:14:56,525
What's going on?

1014
01:14:56,598 --> 01:14:57,907
Go. Just drive.

1015
01:14:57,974 --> 01:14:59,022
What?

1016
01:14:59,094 --> 01:15:00,207
Go. Just drive.

1017
01:15:00,278 --> 01:15:01,227
I'm going. I'm going.
Just drive!

1018
01:15:01,302 --> 01:15:03,244
Come on, lets get
out of here. Go, go!

1019
01:15:03,318 --> 01:15:04,944
Go, go, go, go!

1020
01:15:06,550 --> 01:15:08,373
Jesus, what happened?

1021
01:15:08,439 --> 01:15:10,578
I got the bird.
That's all that matters.

1022
01:15:10,647 --> 01:15:13,036
Oh, God. Were they...
Were they that upset?

1023
01:15:13,111 --> 01:15:14,288
They will be.

1024
01:15:14,359 --> 01:15:15,407
What?

1025
01:15:19,479 --> 01:15:21,999
What happened to
"two birds, one stone"?

1026
01:15:22,071 --> 01:15:23,380
One bird's all
I could manage.

1027
01:15:23,448 --> 01:15:25,815
Eloise, they never would've
given me that bird.

1028
01:15:25,880 --> 01:15:27,571
Trust me.
You don't know that.

1029
01:15:27,640 --> 01:15:29,101
I cut my losses.

1030
01:15:29,175 --> 01:15:30,255
If she wanted this
bird turned loose,

1031
01:15:30,328 --> 01:15:31,605
this is the way
to get it done.

1032
01:15:34,648 --> 01:15:36,339
Okay. All right.

1033
01:15:56,664 --> 01:15:59,698
This isn't animal cruelty
or something, is it?

1034
01:16:02,522 --> 01:16:04,725
It wasn't my idea.
It was your idea.

1035
01:16:04,794 --> 01:16:07,379
It wasn't my idea.
It was her idea.

1036
01:16:08,857 --> 01:16:11,029
Well, lets let him decide.

1037
01:16:53,148 --> 01:16:54,293
Okay.

1038
01:16:57,980 --> 01:17:02,136
This looks like a good place,
so I guess this is goodbye.

1039
01:17:04,892 --> 01:17:06,037
Go on.

1040
01:17:06,812 --> 01:17:08,819
Come on, Rocky.
Fly away.

1041
01:17:09,564 --> 01:17:11,670
Come on, lets go!
Giddyup!

1042
01:17:12,988 --> 01:17:15,923
You'll see the world.
Come on. Meet some girls.

1043
01:17:20,477 --> 01:17:21,819
No, come on.

1044
01:17:22,429 --> 01:17:24,283
Go on, get out of here.

1045
01:17:25,021 --> 01:17:26,843
No, Rock. Come on. Go.

1046
01:17:27,549 --> 01:17:28,826
Come here.

1047
01:17:32,413 --> 01:17:34,551
Fly away.
Rocky, look at me.

1048
01:17:38,333 --> 01:17:40,504
Giddyup! Giddyup!

1049
01:17:42,685 --> 01:17:45,238
All right,
now you're pissing me off.

1050
01:17:45,886 --> 01:17:47,479
You want to go back
to Semper Fi's house?

1051
01:17:49,150 --> 01:17:50,840
All right, you know what?
You're on your own.

1052
01:19:11,361 --> 01:19:12,703
How'd it go?

1053
01:19:13,281 --> 01:19:14,972
Mission accomplished.

1054
01:19:15,041 --> 01:19:16,503
Was he happy?

1055
01:19:19,106 --> 01:19:20,415
Are you happy?

1056
01:19:23,746 --> 01:19:26,201
It's a bird.
I set it free.

1057
01:19:28,098 --> 01:19:29,047
Oh.

1058
01:19:37,186 --> 01:19:39,009
I need you to take me
back to the hotel.

1059
01:19:39,715 --> 01:19:40,892
Okay.

1060
01:19:43,715 --> 01:19:45,504
I feel better
for having done it, okay?

1061
01:19:45,571 --> 01:19:48,637
Listen, you don't have to
talk about it if you
don't want to. Really.

1062
01:19:48,707 --> 01:19:49,852
Just tell me what to say
and I'll say it.

1063
01:19:49,923 --> 01:19:50,905
No.

1064
01:19:51,267 --> 01:19:52,477
I don't... I don't know.
I'm not good...

1065
01:19:52,547 --> 01:19:54,238
I haven't thought
this through.

1066
01:19:55,491 --> 01:19:58,459
You know, Burke,
I like you. I like you.

1067
01:19:59,299 --> 01:20:00,576
Not the author.

1068
01:20:01,092 --> 01:20:02,368
Not the guy
with the microphone.

1069
01:20:02,435 --> 01:20:04,093
And I just...
I just want to help.

1070
01:20:05,348 --> 01:20:07,770
You know what, Eloise,
I just...

1071
01:20:08,612 --> 01:20:11,776
I need you to take me
back to the hotel, right now,

1072
01:20:12,196 --> 01:20:13,789
and I need you
to respect that.
Burke, I will...

1073
01:20:13,860 --> 01:20:16,860
Damn it!
You just don't know
when to quit, do you?

1074
01:20:16,933 --> 01:20:19,682
I asked you to stop
and you just keep on.

1075
01:20:20,548 --> 01:20:23,036
Maybe you're the one
who needs psychoanalysis.

1076
01:20:23,108 --> 01:20:25,050
Leave me alone,
all right?

1077
01:20:27,333 --> 01:20:29,504
I can catch
my own ride back.

1078
01:21:13,543 --> 01:21:15,233
It's about time.

1079
01:21:15,783 --> 01:21:17,922
Oh, my God!
Where the hell
have you been?

1080
01:21:17,991 --> 01:21:19,584
It's not important.
Uh-huh.

1081
01:21:19,655 --> 01:21:21,215
Well, let me
tell you something
that is important.

1082
01:21:21,287 --> 01:21:23,229
You blew off dinner
and Vernon's here.

1083
01:21:23,303 --> 01:21:24,448
I mean, Jesus,
you have got to...

1084
01:21:24,519 --> 01:21:25,796
Lane!

1085
01:21:29,640 --> 01:21:32,258
I'll meet with him
first thing in the morning,
make sure he feels the love.

1086
01:21:32,327 --> 01:21:34,269
You, meanwhile,
accept their offer,

1087
01:21:34,343 --> 01:21:35,837
but tell them the DVD
rollout is too late.

1088
01:21:35,911 --> 01:21:37,537
I want it bumped up
to next month.

1089
01:21:39,560 --> 01:21:40,804
Jesus.

1090
01:21:42,280 --> 01:21:44,451
What the hell
happened to you, man?

1091
01:21:44,520 --> 01:21:46,014
I can't wait to
get out of this city.

1092
01:21:47,625 --> 01:21:48,770
Hey!

1093
01:21:49,704 --> 01:21:50,816
Is everything cool?

1094
01:21:50,888 --> 01:21:52,383
Absolutely.

1095
01:21:52,456 --> 01:21:54,758
Yeah? Anything of note
happen this afternoon?

1096
01:21:54,824 --> 01:21:55,773
Not particularly.

1097
01:21:55,849 --> 01:21:56,994
What about Eloise?

1098
01:21:57,288 --> 01:22:00,550
Stop! Wait! Listen to me.

1099
01:22:01,577 --> 01:22:04,993
You know, you can
talk to me if you want to.

1100
01:22:06,730 --> 01:22:09,828
I know. I get all mixed up.
I get caught up
in this business shit,

1101
01:22:09,897 --> 01:22:11,686
but I want you to know

1102
01:22:13,257 --> 01:22:15,428
that I'm there for you
if you need me to be.

1103
01:22:18,569 --> 01:22:19,780
She's gone.

1104
01:22:19,946 --> 01:22:21,539
She's gone?
What do you mean,
she's gone?

1105
01:22:23,754 --> 01:22:26,056
I don't know, man, I just...

1106
01:22:26,122 --> 01:22:27,683
I screwed it up.

1107
01:22:29,322 --> 01:22:32,835
I threw all my...
All my bullshit in her face.

1108
01:22:34,954 --> 01:22:36,962
It could've been something.

1109
01:22:38,634 --> 01:22:40,423
Night, Lane.
Burke.

1110
01:22:41,387 --> 01:22:43,045
Sleep well.
Big day tomorrow.

1111
01:22:43,114 --> 01:22:44,096
Burke.

1112
01:22:45,867 --> 01:22:47,143
Burke.

1113
01:23:03,787 --> 01:23:04,900
She'd be
proud of you.

1114
01:23:04,972 --> 01:23:05,954
I didn't go
to her funeral.

1115
01:23:06,028 --> 01:23:07,010
Hypocrite.

1116
01:23:07,084 --> 01:23:08,131
You're stuck.

1117
01:23:08,204 --> 01:23:09,731
You can't move
forward because

1118
01:23:09,804 --> 01:23:11,265
you've got your eyes
on the rearview mirror.

1119
01:23:11,340 --> 01:23:12,420
You're
really messed up.

1120
01:23:12,492 --> 01:23:13,801
Swerved into a pole.

1121
01:23:13,868 --> 01:23:15,526
She died instantly.

1122
01:23:18,860 --> 01:23:21,479
When are you gonna stop
lying, son?

1123
01:24:05,102 --> 01:24:07,110
Good morning, sire.
This way.

1124
01:24:07,183 --> 01:24:08,165
What happened to you?

1125
01:24:08,239 --> 01:24:10,126
Went for a little run.
It's refreshing.

1126
01:24:10,190 --> 01:24:13,802
You know, Vernon went
for the international
and DVD rollout.

1127
01:24:13,870 --> 01:24:16,805
Yeah. Old man
likes what he sees
and we are Rolls-Royce.

1128
01:24:16,879 --> 01:24:18,156
Get it done.
First things first,

1129
01:24:18,223 --> 01:24:20,808
I need you to
shake some hands
with somebody here.

1130
01:24:22,191 --> 01:24:23,620
Mr. Vernon,
it's a pleasure...

1131
01:24:32,048 --> 01:24:33,870
Lane goddamn Marshall.

1132
01:24:39,600 --> 01:24:40,844
Well,

1133
01:24:43,760 --> 01:24:45,549
this is unexpected.

1134
01:24:50,352 --> 01:24:51,726
I'm sorry.

1135
01:24:53,200 --> 01:24:56,681
Lane told me the truth.

1136
01:25:01,553 --> 01:25:05,230
You don't deserve
what you put
yourself through.

1137
01:25:08,305 --> 01:25:10,029
I hope that
you can find a way

1138
01:25:10,098 --> 01:25:12,945
to somehow give
yourself a break

1139
01:25:14,353 --> 01:25:17,931
because if you don't,
this is... This is
gonna be your life.

1140
01:25:20,850 --> 01:25:22,705
I just think that's...

1141
01:25:24,690 --> 01:25:26,414
That's just sad.

1142
01:25:30,002 --> 01:25:31,825
That's it. That's...

1143
01:25:32,914 --> 01:25:34,824
That's all I came to say.

1144
01:25:42,419 --> 01:25:45,419
So, just take care
of yourself, okay?

1145
01:26:04,596 --> 01:26:06,221
How's about it,
folks, huh?

1146
01:26:07,411 --> 01:26:10,129
Has it been a week
of miracles or what?

1147
01:26:13,780 --> 01:26:17,839
How many of you
can't get enough
of Burke Ryan?

1148
01:26:19,796 --> 01:26:22,666
I bet that you
would love to see him

1149
01:26:22,740 --> 01:26:25,839
in your living room
from 3:00 p.m.
to 4:00 p.m. every day

1150
01:26:25,908 --> 01:26:27,599
on your local
syndicated channel.

1151
01:26:27,668 --> 01:26:30,254
Huh? Yes!

1152
01:26:32,309 --> 01:26:34,765
We'll see what we
can do about that.

1153
01:26:34,836 --> 01:26:40,750
Now, without further ado,
the man of the hour,
Burke Ryan.

1154
01:26:58,262 --> 01:27:00,629
Thank you.
Please have a seat.

1155
01:27:01,750 --> 01:27:04,052
Thank you.
Have a seat, please.

1156
01:27:06,198 --> 01:27:07,573
Gosh, I'm...

1157
01:27:09,143 --> 01:27:10,899
I'm feeling okay.
How are you?

1158
01:27:10,966 --> 01:27:12,428
A-Okay!

1159
01:27:16,567 --> 01:27:17,844
Sir, I need to
see your badge.

1160
01:27:17,911 --> 01:27:19,471
I'm sorry, what?
Sir, your badge.

1161
01:27:19,543 --> 01:27:22,413
I got a badge.
He's a damn thief,
you know.

1162
01:27:22,743 --> 01:27:24,204
Son of a bitch
broke into my house
and took something.

1163
01:27:24,279 --> 01:27:25,588
There's your badge.
You can keep it.

1164
01:27:25,655 --> 01:27:26,703
You keep it!

1165
01:27:26,776 --> 01:27:30,037
We have made
a lot of progress
in the last few days,

1166
01:27:31,224 --> 01:27:32,817
but don't forget,

1167
01:27:33,559 --> 01:27:35,217
it's just a foundation
for the future.

1168
01:27:40,056 --> 01:27:41,463
Excuse me.

1169
01:27:49,720 --> 01:27:52,622
You know...
Boy, I'm sorry.

1170
01:27:56,889 --> 01:27:58,547
I... I've...

1171
01:28:03,768 --> 01:28:06,005
I can't lie
to you guys anymore.

1172
01:28:10,745 --> 01:28:12,600
You know, I stand here

1173
01:28:14,874 --> 01:28:17,743
and I watch you all
confront your pain.

1174
01:28:21,657 --> 01:28:23,151
And I envy you

1175
01:28:24,793 --> 01:28:26,135
because

1176
01:28:29,338 --> 01:28:31,345
I haven't confronted mine.

1177
01:28:38,138 --> 01:28:40,375
I didn't want it
to be my fault.

1178
01:28:41,339 --> 01:28:43,127
My wife's accident.

1179
01:28:45,275 --> 01:28:46,835
It was raining.

1180
01:28:48,667 --> 01:28:50,074
This dog

1181
01:28:55,708 --> 01:28:57,846
in the middle of the road.

1182
01:29:00,475 --> 01:29:02,199
We had been arguing

1183
01:29:04,219 --> 01:29:07,602
over paint colors
for the kitchen.

1184
01:29:11,292 --> 01:29:12,721
Paint colors.

1185
01:29:19,004 --> 01:29:21,175
But what I haven't told you

1186
01:29:29,020 --> 01:29:31,476
is that I was
driving the car,

1187
01:29:34,909 --> 01:29:36,087
not her.

1188
01:29:43,901 --> 01:29:45,527
I killed my wife.

1189
01:29:57,502 --> 01:29:59,324
I'm so sorry.

1190
01:30:09,375 --> 01:30:11,546
It was just
an accident, son.

1191
01:30:16,575 --> 01:30:18,168
That's all it was.

1192
01:30:29,311 --> 01:30:31,100
There was nothing
you could have done.

1193
01:30:31,167 --> 01:30:32,116
No.

1194
01:30:32,191 --> 01:30:33,140
No, it's true.

1195
01:30:33,216 --> 01:30:36,063
It was just one of those
freak accidents.

1196
01:30:36,544 --> 01:30:39,195
Listen to me.
We never blamed you.

1197
01:30:40,448 --> 01:30:41,725
Never.

1198
01:30:42,079 --> 01:30:45,243
All we really wanted to do
was mourn with you, son.

1199
01:30:45,312 --> 01:30:48,126
We didn't know what to do.
We couldn't find you.

1200
01:30:48,192 --> 01:30:50,297
That's been the worst part.

1201
01:30:59,041 --> 01:31:00,502
It's okay.

1202
01:32:13,924 --> 01:32:17,339
Hey. Come here.

1203
01:32:21,220 --> 01:32:25,311
I was thinking that maybe
I should've had you do that
a long time ago.

1204
01:32:28,964 --> 01:32:30,175
You gonna be all right?

1205
01:32:30,245 --> 01:32:31,587
Yeah, in time.

1206
01:32:31,717 --> 01:32:34,368
Mr. Ryan? Ted Vernon.

1207
01:32:35,429 --> 01:32:37,850
That was something.

1208
01:32:39,301 --> 01:32:41,210
Yeah, that was
something, huh?

1209
01:32:41,285 --> 01:32:44,132
That was reality
up there, Mr. Vernon.

1210
01:32:44,198 --> 01:32:47,264
And if you can't accept
that for what it is,

1211
01:32:47,333 --> 01:32:50,977
then you can take
your deal and you can
shove it up your ass.

1212
01:32:54,661 --> 01:32:59,483
I found it refreshing
and I respect you for it.

1213
01:33:03,430 --> 01:33:04,772
Thank you.

1214
01:33:05,478 --> 01:33:07,005
I'm sorry. Are we still...

1215
01:33:07,335 --> 01:33:08,317
We'll see.

1216
01:33:09,607 --> 01:33:10,948
This is why
you keep firing me.

1217
01:33:11,015 --> 01:33:12,837
I'll be right back.
Mr. Vernon?

1218
01:33:28,135 --> 01:33:31,201
There's something
I don't think
you ever realized.

1219
01:33:31,559 --> 01:33:33,381
As far as
we were concerned,

1220
01:33:33,447 --> 01:33:35,270
we didn't just
lose our daughter.

1221
01:33:35,911 --> 01:33:37,635
We also lost our son.

1222
01:33:39,880 --> 01:33:40,829
I'm sorry.

1223
01:33:41,095 --> 01:33:42,044
We understand.

1224
01:33:43,784 --> 01:33:47,100
And she would want you
to just get on
with your life.

1225
01:33:48,232 --> 01:33:49,955
And don't be a stranger.

1226
01:33:50,024 --> 01:33:52,774
But next time
make sure you use
the front door.

1227
01:33:52,840 --> 01:33:54,564
I will. I promise.

1228
01:33:55,272 --> 01:33:58,851
And listen.
Thank you, son.
Thank you.

1229
01:33:59,592 --> 01:34:01,021
Look, I should have done this
a long time ago.

1230
01:34:01,097 --> 01:34:03,431
No, no, no,
not about that.

1231
01:34:03,497 --> 01:34:05,504
For getting rid
of that damn bird.

1232
01:34:07,177 --> 01:34:08,125
I love you, kid.

1233
01:34:08,201 --> 01:34:09,379
I love you, too.

1234
01:36:53,328 --> 01:36:55,695
Hey, I got your bear grass.

1235
01:36:55,760 --> 01:36:57,833
Oh, great. Thank you. Hi.

1236
01:37:16,081 --> 01:37:17,194
Hi.

1237
01:37:18,673 --> 01:37:19,655
Hi.

1238
01:37:21,105 --> 01:37:22,796
Well, the thing is

1239
01:37:25,553 --> 01:37:27,855
you've spent
the last few days

1240
01:37:27,921 --> 01:37:30,288
getting to know
the part of me that...

1241
01:37:32,018 --> 01:37:34,254
That wasn't
really available.

1242
01:37:34,674 --> 01:37:39,377
So, I was wondering,
if I haven't screwed it up
too bad,

1243
01:37:41,426 --> 01:37:46,511
if you would be interested
in getting to know
the part of me that is.

1244
01:37:48,498 --> 01:37:49,578
Yes, she would.

1245
01:37:50,131 --> 01:37:51,178
Marty!

1246
01:37:51,347 --> 01:37:52,591
Sorry.

1247
01:38:18,036 --> 01:38:19,149
Yes.

1248
01:38:36,244 --> 01:38:38,154
Chapter 15.

1249
01:38:38,229 --> 01:38:39,538
During your travels,

1250
01:38:39,605 --> 01:38:42,671
it's important
to always keep
one thing in mind.

1251
01:38:42,741 --> 01:38:45,873
When one thing ends,
something else begins.

1252
01:39:04,726 --> 01:39:05,937
Jeez.

1253
01:39:08,342 --> 01:39:09,869
Is it yourself?

1254
01:39:11,318 --> 01:39:13,260
Yes, who else would it be?

1255
01:39:15,254 --> 01:39:17,905
Come on, climb on. Come on.

1256
01:39:19,863 --> 01:39:21,423
Hello.
Hello.

1257
01:39:22,487 --> 01:39:25,040
I won't ask you
where you've been,
not that I care.

1258
01:39:25,111 --> 01:39:26,802
Hello.
Hello.

